.SH NAME
SVGGraphicsElement.getScreenCTM \- SVGGraphicsElement: getScreenCTM()
method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[CR]getScreenCTM()\f[R] method of the
\f[CR]SVGGraphicsElement\f[R] interface represents the matrix that
transforms the current element\[cq]s coordinate system to the coordinate
system of the SVG viewport for the SVG document fragment.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
getScreenCTM()
.EE
.SS Parameters
None.
.SS Return value
A \f[CR]DOMMatrix\f[R] object.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Getting the Screen Transformation Matrix
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]svg\f[R] xmlns=\[dq]http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\[dq] width=\[dq]400\[dq] height=\[dq]400\[dq]>
  \f[I]<!\-\- Circle with translation and scale \-\->\f[R]
  <\f[B]circle\f[R]
    id=\[dq]circle\[dq]
    cx=\[dq]50\[dq]
    cy=\[dq]50\[dq]
    r=\[dq]30\[dq]
    fill=\[dq]blue\[dq]
    transform=\[dq]translate(100, 150) scale(2)\[dq] />
</\f[B]svg\f[R]>
.EE
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] circle = document.getElementById(\[dq]circle\[dq]);

\f[I]// Get the current screen transformation matrix\f[R]
